<FIRST>r i PM-BRF--China-Rabies     05-26 0127</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-BRF--China-Rabies,0130</SECOND>
<HEAD>80 People In Eastern Province Die Of Rabies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>BEIJING (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Eighty people died from rabies in the eastern
China province of Shandong during the first three months of this
year, an official daily said today.
   The China Daily quoted a local health official as saying 539
people in the province died from rabies last year.
   The official said there are now 6 million dogs in Shandong
despite a ban on keeping dogs in its urban areas. He said
anti-rabies vaccine is scarce in many rural areas where dogs are
allowed, and many bite victims cannot receive treatment in time.
   There are no national figures for rabies victims. Health
officials in southern Guangdong province earlier reported 566
deaths from rabies in 1987 and 1988.
