<SECOND>AM-Bleacher Collapse,0144</SECOND>
<HEAD>Bleachers Collapse, Injuring 12 During Graduation Ceremonies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FOWLER, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Bleachers collapsed Thursday night at a
high school gymnasium, injuring at least a dozen people watching
graduation ceremonies, a fire official said.
   At least six people suffered major injuries and six were injured
slightly in the accident around 9 p.m. at Fowler High School, said
Assistant Fire Chief Roger Lundy.
   The accident happened as graduation ceremonies for about 30
seniors were ending, Lundy said. ``They were starting the
processional and the spectators stood up and it collapsed,'' he
said.
   Rescuers had to lift bleachers off some victims. Lundy said
rescuers had to lift the bleachers off some of the victims. He said
some of the injured were adults and some were children.
   The injured were taken to hospitals in Pueblo about 30 miles to
the northwest.

