<BYLINE>---</BYLINE>
<HEAD>Hams Recalled That May Be Undercooked</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A Cedar Rapids, Iowa, food processor,
Cedarrapids Meats Inc., has voluntarily recalled an estimated 800
canned hams distributed in 13 states because the meat may be
undercooked, the Agriculture Department said.
   Lester M. Crawford, administrator of the department's Food
Safety and Inspection Service, said the hams _ a total of about
9,000 pounds _ could cause trichinosis if eaten. However, he added,
no illnesses have been reported.
   The hams were distributed to consignees in Arkansas, Florida,
Iowa, Minnesota, Montana, Nebraska, North Carolina, Oklahoma,
Tennessee, Texas, Utah, Vermont and Virginia. Those may have sold
the hams to customers in other states.
   The product was described as canned 11-pound, 4-ounce hams
labeled ``Wilson Continental Deli Ham, Water Added.'' The
establishment number, ``Est. 111'' is printed inside the USDA
inspection seal on the label. Crawford said the hams can be
identified by the code number 0898D embossed on the end of the can.
</TEXT>
