<TEXT>
   A class field trip turned into a visit to the
juvenile detention center for two sixth-graders after they
allegedly helped themselves to more than $10,000 during a bank tour.
   The boys, ages 12 and 13, were charged with grand theft Thursday
after allegedly stuffing $100 bills in their clothes as their class
