about the reported theft one at a time. He said the boys did not
try to deny that they took the money, and all the money was
recovered.
   Nowling later assembled all the sixth-graders for a lecture.
   ``I think (the incident) may have seemed kind of funny to start
out with, but when I got there it ceased being funny,'' Nowling
said.
   He said the boys, both recent transfers to the school, would be
suspended for the rest of the school year.
