<HEAD>Nine Injured When Bleachers Collapse During Graduation</HEAD>
<DATELINE>FOWLER, Colo. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A section of bleachers collapsed during a
high school graduation ceremony and nine spectators were injured,
authorities said.
   ``The minister had just finished the benediction'' Thursday
night when the middle section of the metal-and-wood folding
structure collapsed, said school Superintendent Larry Vibber.
   The injured were transported by ambulance to hospitals in
Pueblo, about 20 miles northwest of this town of about 1,200 people
in eastern Colorado, local fire officials said.
   One woman was in critical care with a head injury; the others
were treated and released.
   The bleachers collapsed about 9 p.m. as the 30 graduating
seniors began to file out of the ceremony and their relatives and
friends stood up to applaud.
   ``There was a lot of whooping and hollering because there were a
lot of kids. They had been kind of excited,'' said Barbara Lotrich,
wife of high school Principal Al Lotrich. ``All of a sudden you see
pushing and shoving and people disappeared.''
   A school board member told everyone to sit down and medical
personnel were summoned to help the injured, Mrs. Lotrich said.
   Rescuers had to lift the bleachers off some of the victims, who
included adults and children.
