<SECOND>PM-BRF--Grandpa's Dog,0158</SECOND>
<HEAD>Grandson Wins Lawsuits Against Grandfather</HEAD>
<DATELINE>DOYLESTOWN, Pa. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A 9-year-old boy attacked by a German
shepherd two years ago has been awarded $909,411 by his
grandparents' insurer.
   The dog owned by the boy's grandparents, Anthony and Cecilia
Recklitis, mauled Brian Fite on July 15, 1987, as he was playing in
their back yard.
   Bucks County Court Judge Paul R. Beckert this week approved an
out-of-court settlement between Fite's parents, Mark and Nancy
Fite, and Allstate Life Insurance, the Recklitis' insurers.
   The boy will receive 48 annual payments beginning on his 18th
birthday in 1997. By 2044 he will have received $909,411.
   ``He was very nearly killed by this dog,'' said the parents'
attorney, Nathan Criste.
   The boy was hospitalized for four days with face and head
injuries that required extensive cosmetic surgery, according to
court records.
   Mrs. Recklitis declined to discuss the suit when contacted at
her home.
</TEXT>
</DOC>
