<FIRST>r a PM-WindowFall     05-26 0287</FIRST>
<SECOND>PM-Window Fall,0294</SECOND>
<HEAD>Tot Thrown Out Of Fifth-Story Window, Police Say; Mother Charged
With Murder</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By VIRGINIA BYRNE</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A mother angry that an air conditioner fell out
of her fifth-story window threw her 2-year-old daughter out after
it, killing the girl, police said.
   The mother, Jessica Sanchez, told police that the tot tumbled
out accidentally after the air conditioner fell Wednesday. But
detectives did not believe her and she was charged Thursday with
murder.
   Two-year-old Rachel Sanchez died Wednesday night at Bronx
Lebanon Hospital of a fractured skull and other broken bones, said
Capt. James J. Campbell.
   Mrs. Sanchez, 29, and her husband, Thomas Sanchez, 33, were also
charged with endangering the welfare of the child, because two
other children, ages 1 and 3, showed signs of abuse, police said.
   They were turned over to state welfare authorities. The couple
also have three older children who live with relatives.
   A neighbor, Valencia Gil, told reporters that the mother had
recently thrown a puppy and two kittens out of a window to punish
the children.
   Under questioning by detectives, Mrs. Sanchez gave conflicting
accounts of how Rachel fell, Campbell said.
   She originally told police that the child had been playing near
an air conditioner when it fell out of the window and the child
tumbled out after it. Later, she said that Rachel was clinging to
her leg, and in an effort to force the child away, the mother shook
her leg so forcefully that the child tumbled away and fell out the
window.
   However, ``the physical layout of the apartment would not be
conducive to that kind of a story,'' Campbell said. ``We feel there
is more to it.''
</TEXT>
