<HEAD>Fixed-Rate Mortgages Slip To 10.5 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Fixed-rate home mortgages averaged 10.5
percent this week, according to a national survey released Friday
by the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corp.
   That was down from a rate of 10.69 percent last week.
   On one-year adjustable rate mortgages, lenders were asking an
average initial rate of 9.18 percent this week, down from 9.28
percent the week before, Freddie Mac said.
