<DATELINE>OMAHA, Neb. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Itzhak Perlman, in town for a sold-out
concert with the Omaha Symphony, said he loves playing the violin
but hates touring.
   ``I don't like to be on tour. I'm in the wrong business,
right?'' said the 43-year-old, world-renowned musician.
   He and his wife, Toby, have five children ranging in age from a
5-year-old in kindergarten to a 20-year-old in college.
   ``I love to play and I love what I do,'' he said Thursday.
``It's just that I'm very much into my family as far as spending
time with them and being a part of what's going on. Especially when
you have young kids, a lot of stuff is happening. So you want to be
part of it.''
   Perlman said he calls home three or four times a day.
