newest data on the state of the economy. The Dow Jones average of
30 industrials slipped 1.28 to 2,482.59.
   The dollar fell in nervous trading.
   Bond prices fell sharply in response to the dollar's decline.
   Grain and soybean prices were mixed; precious metal prices
climbed, livestock and meat prices were mixed, and energy futures
