<HEAD>Yields Fall in 5-Year Note Auction</HEAD>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Yields on five-year Treasury notes fell to the
lowest level since Feb. 25, 1988.
   The average yield in Thursday's auction was 8.72 percent, down
from 9.49 percent at the last auction on Feb. 23.
   It was the lowest rate since five-year notes averaged 7.65
percent on Feb. 25, 1988. The notes will carry a coupon interest
rate of 8| percent with each $10,000 in face value selling for
$9,954.
   A total of $7.51 billion in notes were sold out of bids totaling
$20.75 billion.
