<HEAD>London Shares Higher at Midday in Light Volume</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices were modestly higher at midday Friday
in light volume.
   However, dealers said the approaching start to the three-day
holiday weekend in Britain kept most share price movements confined
to a narrow range.
   ``There's not much business around except for a bit of strength
where there has been a lack of stock in the market or where certain
stocks have had good press coverage lately,'' said one chief
British equities dealer at a large U.S. brokerage firm.
   At about noon in London, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange
100-share index was up 3.8 points, or 0.2 percent, at 2,140.4, off
its early morning best level of 2,143.9, but above the midmorning
minimum of 2,137.6.
   Volume came to a light 274.6 million shares by midday compared
with 278 million shares at the same time Thursday.

