<HEAD>London Shares Rise</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: New thruout with closing figures.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Share prices edged higher Friday in sluggish
trading on the London Stock Exchange.
   Many traders decided to sit out the last session before the
upcoming three-day holiday weekend. ``There was no real impetus for
people to do anything today,'' one trader said.
   At the close, the Financial Times-Stock Exchange 100-share index
rose 3.7 points, or 0.2 percent, to 2,140.3.
   The index lost 64.4 points during the week. Shares were buffeted
Monday and Tuesday by fears of an imminent interest rate hike in
Britain, which materialized on Wednesday when the commercial banks'
raised their base lending rate by one percentage point to 14
percent.
   The Financial Times 30-share index gained 1.5 points on Friday
to close at 1,778.8. The Financial Times 500-share index rose 4.16
points to close at 1,222.91.
   Volume came to 460.9 million shares, down from Thursday's 482.8
million shares.
